The paper discusses the use of Tensor Product Representations (TPRs) for mapping inference in predicate logic to computation, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computational linguistics (cs.CL), machine learning (cs.LG), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper specifically focuses on the bAbI question-answering task, which is a common benchmark for evaluating reasoning abilities of AI systems, further supporting the likelihood of it belonging to these sub-categories.
